\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj{\b\fs24 New River Regional Water Treatment Plant Regulated Substances}{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj{\fs24 
The New River Regional Water Treat}{\fs24 ment Plant is a water treatment facility that takes raw water from the New River in }{\fs24 Beckwith,}{\fs24 
 West Virginia, and treats the water with chlorine and other chemicals to make potable (drinking) quality water for public distribution and consumption.  Sewage t}{\fs24 reatment is not a part of plant operations. The plant handles one }{\fs24 
RMP-regulated}{\fs24  toxic substance above the EPA threshold quantity, which is chlorine. No regulated flammable substances are present at the treatment plant}{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 
\qj{\fs24 Chlorine is delivered to our plant and stored in 1-ton ("ton") containers and is fed to the process from one of the containers at a time. The container storage room can hold up to 6 one-ton}{\fs24 
 containers. One container is connected to the same feed piping manifold. An alternate supply arrangement}{\fs24 
 consists of one additional to

n containers connected to a parallel, but normally isolated, feed piping manifold. Chlorine is stored as a liquefied gas under pressure, fed as a gas to the }{\fs24 chlorinators,}{\fs24 
 and injected as a vapor at the outlet of the into the }{\fs24 water stream. The chlorine process is classified as a Program Level 3 process, and we implement a complete accide}{\fs24 nt prevention program.}{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 
\qj{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 {\b\i\fs24 Offsite}{\b\i\fs24  }{\b\fs24 Consequence Analysis}{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 {\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj\tx144\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040
\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\tx13680\tx14400\tx15120\tx15840\tx16560\tx17280\tx18000\tx18720\tx19440\tx20160\tx20880\tx21600\tx22320\tx23040\tx23760\tx24480\tx25200\tx25920\tx26640{\fs24 
We performed an off-site consequence analysis to estimate the potential for an accidental }{\fs24 
release of chlorine from our facility as a regulated toxic substance that could affect the public or the environment. The off-site consequence analysis consisted of evaluating both a worst-case scenario }{\fs24 (WCS)}{\fs24 
 and an alternative release scenario }{\fs24 (ARS)}{\fs24  foll}{\fs24 owing identification of the appropriate }{\fs24 ARS.}{\fs24  We do not expect a worst-case release scenario to ever occur. An }{\fs24 ARS}{\fs24 
 represents a release that might occur during the lifetime of a facility similar to our water treatment plant. }{\fs24 ARS}{\fs24 \'92}{\fs24 s}{\fs24  can be used to help the }{\fs24 Fayette}{\fs24  (local) Emergency Planning Committee }{\fs24 (FEPC)}{
\fs24  improve and prepare an effective community emergency response plan.}{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj\tx144\tx720{\fs24 \par}
\pard\plain \s75 \fs24\lang1033 \qj\tx144\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200
