We have submitted release scenario analyses to EPA and have shared that information with }{\fs24 FEPC}{\fs24  and other organizations involved in emergenc}{\fs24 
y response activities. It is also available to local residents, schools, hospitals, and businesses. For these events, we have emergency mitigation systems that should help reduce the consequences of the events if they occur. In all cases, if such events o
}{\fs24 c}{\fs24 
cur, we would activate our emergency response plan to respond to the event notify local authorities, and take appropriate actions to protect our employees, contractors, and people in the community. The paragraphs below briefly describe the scenarios we ha
}{\fs24 ve included in our risk management plan }{\fs24 (RMPlan),}{\fs24  including information about the key administrative controls and mitigation measures we have put in place to limit the exposure distances for each scenario.}{\fs24 \par}

